Aim: Consider an examination system. It will accept the marks of 4 subjects. Write procedure which will find the total and average of 4 subjects and display the grade.

Solution:
CREATE OR REPLACE PROCEDURE Sub_Avg (
    cn IN INT, 
    dbms IN INT, 
    ifds IN INT, 
    cmbs IN INT
) AS
    total INT;
    per NUMBER(5,2)

BEGIN
    total := cn + dbms + ifds + cmbs;
    per := (total / 400) * 100;
    
    IF cn < 40 OR dbms < 40 OR ifds < 40 OR cmbs < 40 THEN
        DBMS_OUTPUT.PUT_LINE('FAIL');
    ELSE
        IF per > 75 THEN
            DBMS_OUTPUT.PUT_LINE('GRADE A'); 
        ELSIF per > 65 AND per <= 75 THEN
            DBMS_OUTPUT.PUT_LINE('GRADE B'); 
        ELSIF per > 55 AND per <= 65 THEN
            DBMS_OUTPUT.PUT_LINE('GRADE C');
        ELSE
            DBMS_OUTPUT.PUT_LINE('GRADE D');
        END IF;
        
        DBMS_OUTPUT.PUT_LINE('PERCENTAGE IS ' || per);
    END IF;
END;
/



Explanation:
•	Procedure Name: Sub_Avg
•	Parameters: Accepts marks for 4 subjects (cn, dbms, ifds, cmbs).


•	Calculations:
o	Total: Sum of all subject marks.
o	Percentage: (total / 400) * 100
•	Grade Determination:
o	FAIL if any mark is below 40.
o	GRADE A for percentage > 75.
o	GRADE B for 65 < percentage <= 75.
o	GRADE C for 55 < percentage <= 65.
o	GRADE D for percentage <= 55.
•	Output: Displays grade and percentage.

Outcome:
Students will learn to - 
Create Procedures: Write and implement PL/SQL procedures for processing and analyzing data.
Perform Calculations: Calculate total marks, percentage, and derive grades based on criteria.
Conditional Logic: Apply conditional statements (`IF`, `ELSIF`) to determine results.
Handle Inputs: Accept and process multiple inputs in procedures.
Display Results: Use `DBMS_OUTPUT.PUT_LINE` to output results and feedback.






-------------------------Without Input Taking From The User-----------------------------

CASE 1


SET SERVEROUTPUT ON;

DECLARE
    s1 NUMBER;
    s2 NUMBER;
    s3 NUMBER;
    s4 NUMBER;
    total NUMBER;
    per NUMBER;
BEGIN
    s1 := 75;
    s2 := 45;
    s3 := 52;
    s4 := 75;
    IF s1 < 50 THEN
        DBMS_OUTPUT.PUT_LINE('Result: FAILED IN s1');
    ELSIF s2 < 50 THEN
        DBMS_OUTPUT.PUT_LINE('Result: FAILED IN s2');
    ELSIF s3 < 50 THEN
        DBMS_OUTPUT.PUT_LINE('Result: FAILED IN s3');
    ELSIF s4 < 50 THEN
        DBMS_OUTPUT.PUT_LINE('Result: FAILED IN s4');
    ELSE
        total := s1 + s2 + s3 + s4;
        per := (total/400)*100;

        DBMS_OUTPUT.PUT_LINE('Result: PASS');
        DBMS_OUTPUT.PUT_LINE('Total Marks: ' || total);
        DBMS_OUTPUT.PUT_LINE('Percentage: ' || per);

        IF per > 75 THEN
            DBMS_OUTPUT.PUT_LINE('Division: DISTINCTION');
        ELSIF per > 60 THEN
            DBMS_OUTPUT.PUT_LINE('Division: FIRST DIVISION');
        ELSIF per > 50 THEN
            DBMS_OUTPUT.PUT_LINE('Division: SECOND DIVISION');
        ELSE
            DBMS_OUTPUT.PUT_LINE('Division: PASS');
        END IF;
    END IF;
END;
/


